commit_title: LibUnicode: Optimize the canonical composition algorithm implementation
commit_body:
It now takes O(N) time instead of O(N^2) time. Additionally some always
false conditions are removed.

commit_title: #22244fix typo
AK: Use correct wide integer type for qhat check in UFixedBigIntDivision
commit_body:
Previously, we were assuming that were always on a 64-bit platform,
which is not 100% correct

commit_title: #20060Revert JSQLParser to 4.5
LibPDF: Usedraw_rect()to show debug clipping rects
commit_body:
Using the path rasterizer here is much slower than simply drawing four
lines. This also more accurately shows the (real) clip as the bounding
box is truncated to an int before adding it as a clip rect.Fixes#23056

commit_title: #18798escape wild cards during primary and imported keys loading
LibIPC: Use a simpler encoding for arithmetic values
commit_body:
This is less code, but mostly serves to reduce the amount of methods to
be added to IPC::MessageBuffer in an upcoming patch.

commit_title: HackStudio: Remove adjustment of text range for documentation tooltip
commit_body:
We no longer need to adjust the hovered span's range to get the correct
hovered text. This fixes the "documentation tooltip" feature.

commit_title: #17675read enum values specifically for new added types
LibUnicode: Make unicode data generation logic more relocatable
commit_body:
The previous logic had several checks for Lagom directories and
subdirectories. All we really want to do for these header checks is make
sure that the files end up in an included folder prefixed with
LibUnicode. We also don't need to hard code the path to the generator,
the $<TARGET_FILES> generator expression can create the path for us.

commit_title: LibGfx: Remove unused headers from BitmapFont.{cpp,h}
LibGUI: Account for the row and column headers when painting a TableView
commit_body: Otherwise we'd be drawing all the rows, instead of the ones in view.Fixes#5483.

commit_title: Everywhere: Force linker hash style to be gnu
xxhash.h as of 2c611a76f914828bed675f0f342d6c4199ffee1e:xxhash.h
Add --slow_usecs option to determine when the "long op" message is pr…
commit_body:
…inted

Summary:

This adds the --slow_usecs option with a default value of 1M. Operations that
take this much time have a message printed when --histogram=1, --stats_interval=0
and --stats_interval_seconds=0. The current code hardwired this to 20,000 usecs
and for some stress tests that reduced throughput by 20% or more.

Test Plan:

./db_bench --benchmarks=fillrandom,readrandom --compression_type=lz4 --slow_usecs=100 --histogram=1
./db_bench --benchmarks=fillrandom,readrandom --compression_type=lz4 --slow_usecs=100000 --histogram=1
